Conditions: - 9) This administrative approval is being granted to the institution concerned in the financial year 2025-26 out of the funds sanctioned and available under the State Schemes.

r) Government Decision No.Bhankhas-2014 / Q. 82 / Part-I issued by the Department of Industries, Power and Labour regarding "Manual of Procedure for Office Procurement to be carried out by Government Department" in this regard. \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ / Industry-4, dated 01.12.2016 and the prescribed procedure mentioned in the subsidiary government decisions should be complied with.

The proposed purchase rates are approximate when given administrative approval. Hence, the prices should be fixed at the end of the procurement process. The Commissioner (Medical Education) as well as the Administrator concerned shall ensure that the rate is below the market price and does not exceed the rate at which the supplier concerned has supplied these items elsewhere.

The specifications of the equipment (18911108) should be comprehensive, comprehensive and of such a nature that three tenders can be received from at least three manufacturers / suppliers who can supply the equipment accordingly. Also, the procurement process should be done only after verifying that the technical specifications are not designed to benefit any particular company.
While installing the equipment, it shall be the responsibility of the concerned administrator to ensure that all the equipment is as per the specifications.
Government Decision No.: Yantrakh-2024 / Q. No.208 / Praja-1

&) The ICAR (Medical Education) and the Dean concerned shall ensure that the proposed equipment is not included in any proposal / purchase elsewhere and that the equipment is required by the institution concerned.

While deciding on the purchase of machinery in this regard, it should be ensured that the expenditure does not exceed the provision of grant-in-aid sanctioned under the head of accounts provided for administrative approval.
It will be necessary to show the prices of the main equipment and their accessories as different.
It should be ensured that no new designations are required for this equipment.

10) While deciding on the purchase of machinery in this regard, it should be ensured that the expenditure does not exceed the provision of grant-in-aid sanctioned under the head of accounts provided for administrative approval.
11) Central Vigilance Commission (CVC) guidelines should be followed strictly while executing the entire procurement process.

12) The State Level Procurement Committee shall comply with the provision in the above mentioned judgment, paragraph no. 3.1.2 of the Department of Industry, Power and Labour, dated 01.12.2016, titled "Price Estimation and Price Reasonability" in paragraph no. 3.9.2.9.
